 with only minor deviations reflecting stochastic demographic fluctuations in the agent-based system. The high variance observed during the initial crash (time steps 250-350) compared to later periods suggests the system is highly sensitive to stochastic spatial clustering of herbivores and random demographic events when the population is growing from initial conditions, whereas later dynamics become more deterministic as the population stabilizes against the seasonal resource template."
